modules.description: Provides functions for analyzing model inputs, generating adversarial examples, and evaluating robustness metrics. Operates on structured data including tensors, feature maps, and classification outputs. Used to test model resilience against perturbations and validate safety constraints in AI systems.

Provides operations to parse and inspect neural network configurations, including layer counts, input/output dimensions, and weight/bias values. Works with structured data representing neural network parameters and input statistics. Used to load and analyze NNet models for validation, transformation, or integration with training pipelines.
